HEADWORD: Compiler
<hw>Com*pil"er</hw> <pr>(k⟦ocr⟧m*p⟦imac⟧l"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[OE. <ets>compiluor</ets>; cf. OF. <ets>compileor</ets>, fr. L.
<ets>compilator</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who compiles; esp.,
one who makes books by compilation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Computers)</fld> <def>a computer program that
decodes instructions written in a higher-level computer language to
produce an assembly-language program or an executable program in machine
language.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Compinge</ent>⟦br⟧
